  "local_port": 37950,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best open-source captive portal for a WiFi Hospot?",
  "response": "When setting up a WiFi hotspot with a captive portal, choosing the right open-source solution is crucial for managing user access, authentication, and bandwidth. Here are some of the best open-source captive portal solutions available:\n\n### 1. **CoovaChilli**\n   - **Description**: CoovaChilli is a popular open-source captive portal solution that integrates well with OpenWrt and other Linux-based systems. It provides a range of features including user authentication, bandwidth management, and session control.\n   - **Features**:\n     - RADIUS integration\n     - Bandwidth throttling\n     - Customizable splash pages\n     - Session management\n   - **Use Case**: Ideal for small to medium-sized hotspots, especially for those using OpenWrt.\n\n### 2. **pfSense with Captive Portal**\n   - **Description**: pfSense is a powerful open-source firewall and router platform that includes a built-in captive portal feature. It\u2019s highly customizable and supports various authentication methods.\n   - **Features**:\n     - Multiple authentication methods (Local DB, RADIUS, LDAP)\n     - Bandwidth management\n     - Session control\n     - Customizable splash pages\n   - **Use Case**: Suitable for larger deployments where a robust firewall solution is also needed.\n\n### 3. **OpenNDS**\n   - **Description**: OpenNDS (Open Network Deauthentication Service) is a lightweight, open-source captive portal solution that is easy to configure and deploy. It\u2019s designed for simple yet effective user authentication.\n   - **Features**:\n     - Easy setup and configuration\n     - Customizable splash pages\n     - Support for multiple authentication methods\n     - Session control\n   - **Use Case**: Best for small to medium-sized hotspots with straightforward requirements.\n\n### 4. **WiFiDog**\n   - **Description**: WiFiDog is an open-source captive portal solution that is widely used in community networks and public hotspots. It offers a flexible and scalable solution for user authentication and access control.\n   - **Features**:\n     - RADIUS support\n     - Customizable splash pages\n     - Bandwidth management\n     - Session control\n   - **Use Case**: Ideal for community networks and public hotspots with a need for scalability.\n\n### 5. **NoDogSplash**\n   - **Description**: NoDogSplash is a fork of WiFiDog and is a simple, lightweight captive portal solution. It\u2019s easy to set up and configure, making it a good choice for small deployments.\n   - **Features**:\n     - Easy setup and configuration\n     - Customizable splash pages\n     - Basic authentication\n     - Session control\n   - **Use Case**: Suitable for small hotspots with basic requirements.\n\n### 6. **ChilliSpot**\n   - **Description**: ChilliSpot is an older but still functional captive portal solution that works well with CoovaChilli. It\u2019s designed for simple user authentication and session management.\n   - **Features**:\n     - RADIUS integration\n     - Basic session management\n     - Customizable splash pages\n   - **Use Case**: Best for legacy systems or simple deployments.\n\n### Considerations:\n- **Scalability**: Choose a solution that can scale with your network. pfSense and CoovaChilli are good for larger deployments, while OpenNDS and NoDogSplash are better for smaller setups.\n- **Customization**: If you need highly customizable splash pages and authentication methods, pfSense and WiFiDog are strong candidates.\n- **Ease of Use**: For simplicity and ease of setup, OpenNDS and NoDogSplash are excellent choices.\n\n### Conclusion:\nThe best open-source captive portal for your WiFi hotspot depends on your specific needs, such as the size of your network, the level of customization required, and the ease of setup. **CoovaChilli** and **pfSense** are highly recommended for their robustness and feature sets, while **OpenNDS** and **NoDogSplash** are great for simpler, smaller deployments.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
